Stakeholder Engineer
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/04/30 07:41:54
Ref. JB3045733
Job Description
The Stakeholder Engineer is to assist the Stakeholder Manager in his effort to seek and obtain all the required approvals and permits for all aspects of the design and construction programs.
His main role is to ensure that all technical standards, policies and procedures are adhered to during the process of obtaining the approval, permits and NOCs.
Reporting to the Stakeholder Manager, s/he will be responsible of the following:
* Follow up on queries or clarification required from Stakeholders
* Ensure that permits are effectively monitored and tracked throughout the program period.
* Interact with all internal and external stakeholders.
* Prepare progress presentations and reports.
Skills
Candidates with Engineering Degree or comparable Technical Bachelor's Degree, preferably with a bias towards Infrastructure.
Minimum 8 yrs of experience in large-scale Infrastructure or Rail Transport Systems.
International Experience (Middle East) of working in an Engineering Management Firm or in a construction site environment.
Excellent Oral and Written English language communication skills.
Qualified professional working under limited supervision capable of performing general technical works and manages projects or tasks effectively.
Arabic speakers will have an advantage.
This job is posted in the following Specialties:
